1
00:00:05,621 --> 00:00:13,307
Einstein says, “Reality is an illusion,
albeit a very persistent one.”

2
00:00:13,741 --> 00:00:17,416
[Inconceivable Story of God]

3
00:00:18,032 --> 00:00:22,976
He means what’s conventionally conceived,
the objective world, that reality.

4
00:00:22,976 --> 00:00:26,933
He rightly said, “It’s an illusion”.
He’s right.

5
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:31,498
What we take to be reality here
is an illusion.

6
00:00:32,170 --> 00:00:37,472
And what people think is fictitious
is reality.

7
00:00:38,243 --> 00:00:42,889
Like the Life of Pi movie,
where the man says,

8
00:00:42,889 --> 00:00:46,891
“I’m gonna tell you a story
that will make you believe in God.”

9
00:00:46,905 --> 00:00:53,734
Then he tells, for the sake of this
conversation, an inconceivable story.

10
00:00:53,764 --> 00:00:58,252
He tells this to a Japanese
insurance agent,

11
00:00:58,252 --> 00:01:04,264
who’s saying, “That’s unbelievable.
You’ll never get any money for that.”

12
00:01:04,264 --> 00:01:06,761
“What if I tell you a story
that’s believable?”

13
00:01:06,761 --> 00:01:07,506
“Yes!”

14
00:01:07,506 --> 00:01:10,329
Then he tells a believable story,
and they say,

15
00:01:10,329 --> 00:01:13,470
“Oh, we could give something for that.”

16
00:01:13,470 --> 00:01:18,728
But then the man says, “But of the two
stories I told you, which do you prefer?”

17
00:01:18,785 --> 00:01:22,804
And they go,
“We prefer the unbelievable one.”

18
00:01:22,815 --> 00:01:25,056
That’s what he meant.

19
00:01:25,056 --> 00:01:28,901
The story of God 
is inconceivable.

20
00:01:28,915 --> 00:01:32,390
The story of science, of rational,

21
00:01:32,390 --> 00:01:36,990
appears to be believable
to so-called ‘rational mind’.

22
00:01:36,990 --> 00:01:41,117
But the story of God 
is inconceivable.

23
00:01:41,117 --> 00:01:45,237
Of the two, we prefer
the inconceivable story of God

24
00:01:45,269 --> 00:01:53,176
to the so-called rational narrative
of secular humanist and atheistic science.

25
00:01:53,480 --> 00:02:00,527
Mr. Nietzsche says, “There are no facts,
there are only interpretations.”

26
00:02:00,527 --> 00:02:05,146
We prefer this interpretation.

